{
  "texts": [
    "The MAD (Mutual Assured Destruction) ledger function takes a novel approach by completely discarding the content of blocks on the longest chain that have another chain with the same length (red blocks, Figure 1a).",
    "This ensures that the miner does not receive any transactions fees or MEV.",
    "This approach is in contrast to both NC and Colordag, which simply take the content of all blocks in the longest chain.",
    "The MAD ledger function severely hinders a selfish miner's ability to create an alternative chain, since they would need it to be strictly longer, as ties yield contentless blocks.",
    "This negates any advantage gained from rushing or from bribing petty-compliant miners."
  ]
}